                        <div class="sing">
                            <div class="sing_date">January 10, 2013<span class="sing_by"> BY joed</span></div>
                            <div class="sing_title">Sharing Scores/Box Scores</div>
                            <div class="sing_content"><p>For the past several weeks we have been testing a new feature that will allow scores &amp; XML box scores to be shared amongst SIDEARM Schools.  This process should eliminate the need to share XML files via email and away team SID&#8217;s will no longer need to worry about updating their sites with scores/xml files.</p>
<p>This feature is being rolled out on Friday, January 11, 2013.</p>
<p>Most importantly, while we believe this is a great value to all schools, we will not force any client to use this feature.  If you do wish not to use this feature you can either turn it off (explained below), or email our support team and we will turn it off for you.</p>
<p>Here is how it works:</p>
<ol start="1">
<li>After an event, the home team uploads the XML box score or updates the score/game result.</li>
<li>If the away team happens to be a SIDEARM School then we will automatically update the score/game result on the away team&#8217;s schedule.</li>
<li>If the home team uploads an XML box score, we will automatically upload that box score to the SIDEARM away team.  The system will also update the cumulative stats/roster bio stats on the SIDEARM away team.  <strong>Note:</strong> it may take a few minutes for the stats/box score to show on the away team site.</li>
<li>In the event that the home team finds any errors within 24 hours, and uploads a new XML box score, we will update the away team box score and stats.</li>
</ol>
<p>For the best results, verify that you have your global opponents setup in your schedules.  If you have submitted your schedules to the NCAA via SIDEARM, then this would already be setup. Since this feature uses the Global ID, it is available for all clients, NCAA, NAIA and NJCAA, etc.</p>
<p>Ultimately this process helps your fellow SID&#8217;s from other SIDEARM Schools and they in return will be helping you.</p>
<p>As noted above, if you wish not to opt-in to this new feature you can:</p>
<ol start="1">
<li>E-Mail support and let them know if you want both or just one of the options turned off.</li>
<li>Starting on Friday, you can go under a settings group named SIDEARM Settings, where you will find two settings that control the opt-in/opt-out of this feature.</li>
</ol>
<ul>
<ul>
<li>Accept Results From Other Sidearm Schools (true/false)</li>
<li>Accept XML Box scores From Other Sidearm Schools (true/false).   <strong>Note: </strong>if you do not wish to use XML box scores on your site, set this to false.</li>
</ul>
</ul>
<p>As a final note, if  for some reason you choose to &#8220;opt-out&#8221; of this feature, you will not receive any scores or box scores from other SIDEARM schools.  However, any scores or box scores that you update will continue to be shared amongst your SIDEARM school opponents. You can also choose to &#8220;opt-in&#8221; at a later date if you wish to, this is not a &#8220;one-time&#8221; deal, just a regular feature being added into your software.</p>
<p>As always let us know if you have any trouble or have any questions.  We look forward to your feedback!</p>
